SPM Modular Project - Module 1: Partition Mapping Kernel
========================================================
Author: Kazi Sohrab Uddin Titu

Description
-----------
Vectorized key-to-partition mapping using multiply-shift hash.
Given N uint64_t keys and P partitions (power of two), computes a
partition ID for each key using a multiply-shift hash function.

Two hash strategies (compile-time selectable):
  - 32-bit hash (default): extracts upper 32 bits of each key, multiplies
    by Knuth's 32-bit constant (0x9E3779B9), shifts right by (32 - log2(P)).
    Lighter compute, vectorizes efficiently with AVX2.
  - 64-bit hash (-DHASH64): full 64-bit multiply by Knuth's golden ratio
    constant (0x9E3779B97F4A7C15), shifts right by (64 - log2(P)).
    Better hash quality but requires emulated 64x64 multiply in AVX2.

Three implementations per hash strategy:
  1. partition_map_baseline : plain C++, auto-vectorization disabled
  2. partition_map_autovec  : plain C++ (same source), auto-vectorization enabled
  3. partition_map_avx2     : hand-written AVX2 intrinsics

Build
-----
  make            # builds 32-bit hash binaries (baseline, autovec, avx2)
  make all64      # builds 64-bit hash binaries (*_64 suffix)
  make vec-report    # GCC vectorization reports for 32-bit hash
  make vec-report-64 # GCC vectorization reports for 64-bit hash
  make clean      # removes all binaries and report files

Run
---
  # 32-bit hash (default)
  ./partition_map_baseline N P [seed] [num_runs]
  ./partition_map_autovec  N P [seed] [num_runs]
  ./partition_map_avx2     N P [seed] [num_runs]

  # 64-bit hash
  ./partition_map_baseline_64 N P [seed] [num_runs]
  ./partition_map_autovec_64  N P [seed] [num_runs]
  ./partition_map_avx2_64     N P [seed] [num_runs]

Arguments:
  N        - number of keys (e.g. 100000000 for 100M)
  P        - number of partitions, must be power of 2 (e.g. 256)
  seed     - PRNG seed for reproducible key generation (default: 42)
  num_runs - number of benchmark repetitions (default: 11)

Example (on the spmcluster, node09):
  srun -p gpu-shared -w node09 ./partition_map_baseline 100000000 256
  srun -p gpu-shared -w node09 ./partition_map_autovec  100000000 256
  srun -p gpu-shared -w node09 ./partition_map_avx2     100000000 256
  srun -p gpu-shared -w node09 ./partition_map_baseline_64 100000000 256
  srun -p gpu-shared -w node09 ./partition_map_autovec_64  100000000 256
  srun -p gpu-shared -w node09 ./partition_map_avx2_64     100000000 256

Correctness Verification
------------------------
Each run prints a position-sensitive XOR checksum. All three binaries
of the same hash variant must produce the same checksum for the same
(N, P, seed).

The AVX2 binaries always verify their output against the scalar
implementation before benchmarking.

Vectorization Report
--------------------
Run 'make vec-report' or 'make vec-report-64' to generate:
  vec_optimized_32.txt / vec_optimized_64.txt - vectorized loops
  vec_missed_32.txt    / vec_missed_64.txt    - missed loops (with reasons)

Design Choices
--------------
Hash function: multiply-shift hash using Knuth's golden ratio constant.
  Two variants provided to compare vectorization effectiveness:
  - 32-bit: single _mm256_mullo_epi32, processes 8 keys/iteration
  - 64-bit: emulated via three _mm256_mul_epu32, processes 4 keys/iteration

Key generation: splitmix64 PRNG (deterministic from seed).

Project Structure
-----------------
  Modulo1_KaziSohrabUddinTitu/
  ├── Makefile
  ├── README
  ├── src/
  │   ├── partition_map.cpp       # plain C++ (baseline + autovec)
  │   ├── partition_map_avx2.cpp  # AVX2 intrinsics version
  │   ├── keygen.hpp              # deterministic key generation
  │   ├── verify.hpp              # checksum + element-wise verification
  │   └── hpc_helpers.hpp         # timing macros + benchmarking stats
  └── report/
      ├── report.tex              # LaTeX source
      └── report.pdf              # compiled PDF report
